title: Elliot Grainge
summary: Elliot Grainge (born November 6, 1993) is a British record executive. He is the founder and CEO of 10K Projects, an independent record label. His label represents hip hop and rap artists including Trippie Redd, Tekashi 6ix9ine, and Iann Dior. Grainge is the son of Universal Music Group executive Lucian Grainge. He is married to social media personality and model Sofia Richie.
